    9: 
   10: ### Fixed — Asset Swap: per-frame "already loaded" AssetBundle flood (#992)
   11: - **Per-frame Unity error flood `The AssetBundle '…sw-rep-clone-engineer' can't be loaded because another AssetBundle with the same files is already loaded`** — `AssetSwapSystem.LoadBundle` called `AssetBundle.LoadFromFile` and, when the LRU cache (max 10) evicted+Unloaded a bundle that Unity still considered loaded (Unload lag / scene-transition skip), the next frame's re-load threw and Unity logged the error. Because the swap retries every pending request each frame, this repeated forever — **740 occurrences** in a single skirmish run, flooding `Player.log` and degrading the game. Fixes in `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`: (1) **already-loaded recovery** — `LoadBundle` now catches the "already loaded" throw and reuses the existing handle via `AssetBundle.GetAllLoadedAssetBundles()` (matched by bundle name), re-caching it so later passes hit the cache and never re-call `LoadFromFile`; (2) **negative-result cache** (`_permanentlyFailedBundles`) — a bundle that yields no usable Mesh/Material (the 13 #986 90-byte stubs) or hard-fails to load is marked permanently failed and skipped on every later frame (logged once, then silent), cleared on `ScheduleReset` so hot-reloaded fixed bundles retry. Live-verified after deploy (build hash `CEA2362E…`, clean skirmish): `Player.log` "already loaded" count **740 → 0** (entire 2273-line run, 0 occurrences, 0 clone-engineer mentions, 0 AssetBundle errors). Working swaps intact — **306 `entity swap result=True`**, ground units `swapped 100/100` across 17264 matching entities, `sw-rep-clone-engineer` cim swap `result=True`. File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`.
   12: ### Fixed — SW building stub bundles built real (#982)
   13: - **12 remaining Star Wars BUILDING bundles were 90-byte stubs** — `sw-assembly-line`, `sw-blast-wall`, `sw-durasteel-barrier`, `sw-guard-tower`, `sw-heavy-foundry`, `sw-mining-facility`, `sw-processing-plant`, `sw-skyshield-generator`, `sw-tech-union-lab`, `sw-tibanna-refinery`, `sw-vulture-nest`, `sw-weapons-factory`. As placeholders they kept those buildings native in-game and made the swap engine (#986) re-load a useless stub every frame, flooding the AssetSwap log with "another AssetBundle with the same files is already loaded". Built REAL Unity 2021.3.45f1 AssetBundles for all 12 (each ~46-47 KB, up from 90 B) — distinct procedural SW-styled building silhouettes (factory / wall / tower / refinery / mine / lab / shield-emitter / vulture-nest / blast-barrier) on a faction-tinted Standard material (CIS grey / Republic white). New self-contained Editor builder `BuildSwBuildingBundles.cs` (meshes generated in-C# via `CombineInstance` of box primitives — no Blender / glTF dependency), promoted to `scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/`. Built headless with the canonical `Unity.exe 2021.3.45f1` (`-batchmode -nographics -quit -executeMethod BuildSwBuildingBundles.Build`), exit 0, bundle headers verified `UnityFS ... 2021.3.45f1`. Bundle filename == `visual_asset` key == Addressable key; all 12 keys were already present in `addressables.yaml` / `asset_pipeline.yaml` (no CRC/hash fields, so no registration change needed). NOT deployed — deploy happens at reconcile.
