   21: ### Fixed — Asset Swap: cims / buildings / aircraft now reskin (#986)
   22: - **Wrong swap archetypes for cims, buildings, and aircraft (live `0 succeeded` → `39 succeeded`)** — The #975 archetype guesses returned 0 RenderMesh-bearing entities, so the `RenderMesh AND <archetype>` swap query matched nothing and these categories logged `batch complete — 0 succeeded, 30 failed` while ground units swapped fine. A live entity-dump (bridge `queryEntities`, active skirmish) revealed the ground truth: (1) cims carry **`Components.Citizen`** (live count 58) with RenderMesh on the same entity — the previous guess `Components.Worker` matched only 2 singletons; (2) DINO **buildings** carry `Components.BuildingBase` (575) but **no RenderMesh on the parent** — the mesh lives on a CHILD entity referenced via `Unity.Entities.LinkedEntityGroup`; (3) `aerial_fighter` resolved to `DINOForge.Runtime.Aviation.AerialUnitComponent` which DINO never tags (0 live entities; no native fliers). Fixes: cims/worker/citizen → `Components.Citizen` (`PackStatMappings`); `aerial_fighter` swap archetype → `Components.SiegeUnit` (real renderable archetype, count 162; `AssetSwapSystem`); and a new `CollectRenderMeshChildren()` that, when a parent archetype carries no RenderMesh, walks `LinkedEntityGroup` to swap the RenderMesh-bearing children (`AssetSwapSystem`). Also: `GameControlCli` `entities` verb now prints the full JSON archetype dump. Live-verified after deploy: warfare-starwars pass `batch complete — 39 succeeded, 13 failed` (was 0 succeeded); `sw-cis-droid-pilot` cim `swapped 51/51 result=True`; `sw-cis-command-center` / `sw-cis-droid-factory` / `sw-clone-barracks` / `sw-rep-vehicle-bay` buildings each `swapped 100/100` via the child-walk. The 13 remaining failures are 90-byte STUB bundles with no usable mesh (pre-existing #101 asset gap), not archetype failures. Survey: `docs/sessions/entity-archetype-survey-20260531.md`. Files: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/PackStatMappings.cs`, `src/Tools/GameControlCli/Program.cs`.
