   24: ### Fixed — Game-Breaking Regression
   25: - **`startGame` RPC corrupting native `GameWorldLoaderSystem` (NRE flood)** — The `startGame` RPC in `GameBridgeServer.HandleStartGame` (introduced by nav-scripter commit 65cddb03) created a bare `Components.SingletonComponents.BeginGameWorldLoadingSingleton` ECS entity with empty/unpopulated fields to programmatically trigger world-load. DINO's native `Systems.GameWorldLoaderSystem.OnUpdate` then called `GetSingleton<>()` expecting the managed component (save path / map id / load params) populated, got null/empty, and threw a `NullReferenceException` **every frame** in `InitializationSystemGroup` — flooding the log and breaking world-load. Fix (safe revert / Option A): the RPC is now a **no-op** that returns `{success:false, disabled:true}` and never creates the bare entity; normal menu-driven world-load is unaffected. To re-enable programmatic world-load, all required singleton fields must be populated with valid values before entity creation. Live-verified: GameWorldLoaderSystem NRE count went from flooding to **0**, game loads a world normally (49014 entities, advancing frames). File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/GameBridgeServer.cs` (~L1841).
