+- **Prevented a live material crash path on HRV2/URP when a swapped bundle material uses legacy shaders** — `TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` now validates the resolved material shader before assigning it to `RenderMesh`. Materials whose shader name is not prefixed with `Universal Render Pipeline/` and that do not expose SRP batcher support via `FindPassTagValue` are skipped from live material assignment, while mesh swaps still proceed when valid. Skipped bundles log once (`[AssetSwap] skipped material swap for X: shader Y not HRV2-compatible`) and fallback to no-op material assignment. Crash-risk runtime writes are therefore prevented without blocking mesh-only swaps. File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`.
+
 ### Fixed — Asset Swap: per-frame "already loaded" AssetBundle flood (#992)
 - **Per-frame Unity error flood `The AssetBundle '…sw-rep-clone-engineer' can't be loaded because another AssetBundle with the same files is already loaded`** — `AssetSwapSystem.LoadBundle` called `AssetBundle.LoadFromFile` and, when the LRU cache (max 10) evicted+Unloaded a bundle that Unity still considered loaded (Unload lag / scene-transition skip), the next frame's re-load threw and Unity logged the error. Because the swap retries every pending request each frame, this repeated forever — **740 occurrences** in a single skirmish run, flooding `Player.log` and degrading the game. Fixes in `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`: (1) **already-loaded recovery** — `LoadBundle` now catches the "already loaded" throw and reuses the existing handle via `AssetBundle.GetAllLoadedAssetBundles()` (matched by bundle name), re-caching it so later passes hit the cache and never re-call `LoadFromFile`; (2) **negative-result cache** (`_permanentlyFailedBundles`) — a bundle that yields no usable Mesh/Material (the 13 #986 90-byte stubs) or hard-fails to load is marked permanently failed and skipped on every later frame (logged once, then silent), cleared on `ScheduleReset` so hot-reloaded fixed bundles retry. Live-verified after deploy (build hash `CEA2362E…`, clean skirmish): `Player.log` "already loaded" count **740 → 0** (entire 2273-line run, 0 occurrences, 0 clone-engineer mentions, 0 AssetBundle errors). Working swaps intact — **306 `entity swap result=True`**, ground units `swapped 100/100` across 17264 matching entities, `sw-rep-clone-engineer` cim swap `result=True`. File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`.
 ### Fixed — SW building stub bundles built real (#982)
